Installing DeSmuME from source



      What is 'SVN' ?

svn <http://subversion.tigris.org/> is a developers tool. It's used to
let multiple developers work on the same codebase without conflicts. If
youre an end-user, don't worry about it. And if you're a developer, see
the question on how to get the latest svn code and build DeSmuME
yourself. See wikipedia
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subversion_(software)> for more info


      What compilers are supported for building DeSmuME from source?

