      Tell me about nitroFS or libFAT

libFAT has been working for quite some time, via MPCF DLDI as mentioned
earlier in the faq. libnds argv is supported. This enables nitroFS to
use libFAT to mount the nds rom, but it expects the rom to exist within
the filesystem at fat:/rom.nds; if you supply a compactflash root
directory equal to /path/to/ where your rom is at /path/to/rom.nds, (and
of course patch w/MPCF), nitroFS will be able to initialize.
Alternatively, use gbaslot-rom=path/to/rom.nds which will also support
nitroFS via its gba-mounting mode.


